---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Home">
  <div class="home-page">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>The Workbench</h1>
    <p>Small software projects around data, coordination, and practical AI.</p>
    <p>This is a place for projects that are useful enough to explain properly. Some are live products. Some are learning projects. All of them are built around the same idea: keep the system understandable, make the work traceable, and avoid making things more complicated than they need to be.</p>
    <p><strong>By Adam Ojrzynski</strong></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card card-feature home-card wide-section">
    <p class="label">LIVE PRODUCT</p>
    <h2>ReadyRoll</h2>
    <p>A no-account scheduling app that helps groups find the best date to meet.</p>
    <p class="narrative-block">ReadyRoll started from a small coordination problem: groups want to meet, but finding a date often turns into a long thread of maybes and reminders.</p>
    <div class="meta-grid">
      <div><p class="meta-label">STATUS</p><p class="meta-value">Live product</p></div>
      <div><p class="meta-label">STACK</p><p class="meta-value">Next.js, TypeScript, Tailwind, Supabase, Vercel</p></div>
      <div><p class="meta-label">FEATURES</p><p class="meta-value">Discord bot integration</p></div>
    </div>
    <p class="card-link-row"><a class="link-arrow" href="/readyroll/">Read about ReadyRoll →</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card card-feature home-card wide-section">
    <p class="label">AGENTS SUITE</p>
    <h2>Agents Suite</h2>
    <p>A growing suite of practical data agents built to understand agent architecture from the ground up.</p>
    <p class="narrative-block">The suite starts with simple local Python agents that do recognisable data work: profiling datasets, reconciling records, and drafting data dictionaries. The aim is to learn where deterministic logic, review loops, and LLM support each belong.</p>
    <div class="meta-grid">
      <div><p class="meta-label">TYPE</p><p class="meta-value">Python CLI agents</p></div>
      <div><p class="meta-label">APPROACH</p><p class="meta-value">Deterministic checks, traceable reports</p></div>
      <div><p class="meta-label">OUTPUT</p><p class="meta-value">Optional LLM polish</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="progression-row">
      <p class="meta-label">PROGRESSION</p>
      <div class="progression-pills" aria-label="Agents suite progression">
        <span>Deterministic CLI</span><i aria-hidden="true">→</i><span>Hybrid local + LLM</span><i aria-hidden="true">→</i><span>Framework agents</span><i aria-hidden="true">→</i><span>Multi-agent workflows</span><i aria-hidden="true">→</i><span>Capstone coordinator</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="card-link-row"><a class="link-arrow" href="/agents/">Explore the suite →</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card card-future home-card wide-section">
    <p class="label">ON THE BENCH</p>
    <h2>Future work</h2>
    <p>This site will grow slowly. New projects will be added when they are mature enough to explain clearly and useful enough to sit alongside the main work.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-principles wide-section">
    <div class="section-heading"><h2>Working Principles</h2></div>
    <ul class="principles-list">
      <li><h3>Useful before impressive</h3><p>Build what solves real problems, not what sounds clever.</p></li>
      <li><h3>Deterministic where possible</h3><p>Prefer predictable logic over probabilistic outputs when you can.</p></li>
      <li><h3>LLMs as support, not source of truth</h3><p>Use AI for polish and suggestions, not as the primary decision maker.</p></li>
      <li><h3>Clear traces, reports, and documentation</h3><p>Make the work visible so others can follow and verify it.</p></li>
      <li><h3>Small systems that are easy to inspect</h3><p>Keep projects simple enough to understand completely.</p></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
